{
  "texts": [
    "Very much situation-specific but learning to know each other helps to accept the differences.",
    "Rather, the lack of any face-to-face-meetings may increase risk of errors and overlooking things, especially those of cultural nature.",
    "Very useful in initially building of teams, but less necessary as the teams get used to working together.",
    "The prevention of conflicts can be easily handled through a face-toface meeting.",
    "No problems provided that face-to-face meeting are feasible and the corresponding travelling costs can be covered."
  ]
}